- Set up Ubuntu VM in VirtualBox
- Enabled SSH service (port 22)
- Configured NAT port forwarding (2222 → 22)
- Connected from Windows using SSH

Windows (SSH Client)
    ↓
localhost:2222
    ↓
VirtualBox NAT Port Forwarding
    ↓
Ubuntu VM :22 (SSH Server)

- SSH is used for remote server control
- Port 22 is default SSH port
- Port forwarding allows external access to VM services
- Service must be running before connection works

Successfully accessed Linux VM remotely via SSH from Windows host.
